UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 973
1 Christian heritage that undergirds American exceptionalism, publicly proclaiming his
2 faith in Jesus Christ as a guiding force in the pursuit of justice, moral clarity, and defense
3 of the unborn; and
4 WHEREAS, as a tireless free speech advocate, Charlie Kirk fought against
5 suppression by technology companies, university indoctrination, and government
6 overreach, ensuring that dissenting voices, especially those of the next generation, could
7 flourish in the public square, thereby preserving the First Amendment of the Constitution
8 of the United States as the bedrock of a free society; and
9 WHEREAS, through relentless persecution, cancellation attempts, smears, and his
10 ultimate assassination, Charlie Kirk became a martyr for truth and liberty, enduring
11 personal and professional attacks with an unwavering resolve to expose corruption,
12 challenge prevailing narratives, and uphold objective reality in the face of censorship and
13 cultural decay; and
14 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk will be remembered for his many contributions to his
15 family, community, and nation, and will be deeply missed by all whose lives were
16 touched by his presence;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
19 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate Kentucky Route 18 in
20 Boone County, from its intersection with Kentucky Route 338 at mile point 0 to the
21 Kentucky Route 237 underpass at mile point 11.776, as the "Charlie Kirk Memorial
22 Highway" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this Resolution, erect
23 appropriate signage denoting this designation.
